Imports the Gaussian Naive Bayes algorithm.
This algorithm is used for classification tasks.

from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score
Imports evaluation metrics:
confusion_matrix → shows correct and incorrect predictions
accuracy_score → calculates accuracy
precision_score → calculates precision
recall_score → calculates recall

data = pd.read_csv("C:\\Users\\raunak\\Downloads\\iris.csv")
Reads the CSV file using pandas.
Stores dataset into variable data.
read_csv() loads data from CSV format.

print(data.head())
Displays first 5 rows of dataset.
Used to check whether data loaded correctly.

X = data.iloc[:, :-1]
Selects all rows and all columns except last column.
X contains input features.
In Iris dataset:
Sepal length
Sepal width
