-1 means last column.

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
X, y, test_size=0.25, random_state=42
)
Purpose
Splits dataset into training and testing parts.
Variables
X_train → training input data

X_test → testing input data

y_train → training output labels

y_test → testing output labels
Parameters
test_size=0.25

25% data used for testing

75% data used for training

random_state=42

Fixes random splitting.

Gives same result every time code runs.

model = GaussianNB()
Creates object of Gaussian Naive Bayes classifier.
model variable stores the algorithm.

model.fit(X_train, y_train)
Trains the model using training data.
fit() teaches the algorithm patterns from dataset.

y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
Predicts output using test data.
Predicted values stored in y_pred.

print("Predictions:", y_pred)
Prints predicted class labels.

cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
Creates confusion matrix.
Compares actual values (y_test) with predicted values (y_pred).
Confusion Matrix contains
TP → True Positive

TN → True Negative

FP → False Positive

FN → False Negative

print("\nConfusion Matrix:\n", cm)
Displays confusion matrix.

\n means new line.

accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
Calculates accuracy of model.
Formula
Accuracy= 
TP+TN/FP+FN+TP+TN
​
precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred, average='macro')
Calculates precision.
Formula
Precision= 
TP/TP+FP

average='macro'
Calculates precision for all classes separately.
Then finds average.

recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred, average='macro')
Calculates recall.
Formula
Recall= TP/TP+FN

​error_rate = 1 - accuracy
Calculates error rate.
Formula
Error Rate=1−Accuracy

print("\nAccuracy:", accuracy)
Prints accuracy value.

